# @primer/react Usage

ALL web apps use `@primer/react` as the ONLY design system. Follow the official documentation exactly.

## Mandatory Rules

- ALWAYS use Primer components instead of raw HTML elements
- NEVER create custom components that duplicate Primer functionality
- NEVER override Primer component internals with custom CSS
- Use `ThemeProvider` at the app root â€” all theming via Primer tokens
- Primer components handle their own styling â€” use component props (`variant`, `size`, `weight`, etc.)
- Before using arbitrary values (e.g. `text-[0.625rem]`), ALWAYS check if the Primer component has a prop for it (e.g. `<Text size="small">`)
- Layout/spacing around Primer components via SCSS Modules + Tailwind @apply (see styling-conventions rule)

## Primer-First Hierarchy

ALWAYS prefer Primer components over native HTML tags. Before writing ANY HTML element, check if Primer has an equivalent:

| Native HTML | Primer Replacement | Usage |
|-------------|-------------------|-------|
| `<button>` | `<Button>`, `<IconButton>` | ALL visible buttons |
| `<span>` | `<Text as="span">` | ALL inline text and icon wrappers |
| `<p>` | `<Text as="p">` | ALL paragraph text |
| `<h1>`â€“`<h6>` | `<Heading as="h1">` etc. | ALL headings |
| `<input>` | `<TextInput>` | ALL text inputs |
| `<select>` | `<Select>` | ALL selects |
| `<img>` | `<Avatar>` | Profile images |
| `<a>` | `<Link>` (TanStack) | ALL navigation links |

### Native HTML Allowed ONLY For

- `<div>` â€” generic layout containers (no Primer equivalent for arbitrary wrappers)
- `<nav>`, `<aside>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<header>`, `<footer>` â€” semantic landmarks
- `<form>` â€” form wrappers
- Invisible/non-visual elements (e.g., backdrop overlay when Primer has no equivalent)

### The Check

Before writing any native HTML tag:
1. Does Primer have a component for this? â†’ **Use it**
2. Does the native tag have a semantic purpose Primer can't fill? â†’ **Allowed**
3. Neither? â†’ **Use Primer's closest equivalent with `as` prop**

```tsx
// BAD â€” native tags when Primer has equivalents
<button onClick={handleClick}>Save</button>
<span className={styles.wrapper}><Icon /></span>
<p>Description text</p>

// GOOD â€” Primer components
<Button onClick={handleClick}>Save</Button>
<Text as="span" className={styles.wrapper}><Icon /></Text>
<Text as="p">Description text</Text>
```

## Colors â€” Primer Theme via useTheme

ALL colors come from Primer's theme object via `useTheme`. Primer's built-in CSS variables (`--bgColor-*`, `--fgColor-*`) do NOT work directly in the DOM. Instead, use `useTheme` to get colors from the JS theme object and inject them as `--primer-*` CSS custom properties via the `style` prop.

The `style` prop is allowed ONLY for injecting `--primer-*` color variables. NEVER for layout, spacing, or sizing.

### Centralized Color Injection

Colors are injected once at the Shell module level (or top-level orchestrator). All descendant components consume them via `var(--primer-*)` in SCSS.

```tsx
import { useTheme } from '@primer/react'
import { buildThemeVars } from './Shell.utils'

const Shell = ({ children }: ShellProps) => {
  const { theme } = useTheme()
  const themeVars = buildThemeVars(theme?.colors)

  return <div style={themeVars}>{children}</div>
}
```

```scss
// In any descendant SCSS
.root {
  background-color: var(--primer-canvas-default);
  color: var(--primer-fg-default);
  border: 1px solid var(--primer-border-default);
}
```

NEVER use Tailwind color utilities (`bg-neutral-*`, `text-white`). NEVER use hardcoded hex/rgb/hsl values. NEVER use Primer CSS vars directly (`var(--bgColor-*)`).

### Overriding Primer Component Styles

When Primer's `variant` prop doesn't provide the needed visual, use `variant="invisible"` + `className` with doubled selector for specificity:

```tsx
<IconButton variant="invisible" className={styles.toggleButton} ... />
```

```scss
.toggleButton.toggleButton {
  background-color: var(--primer-neutral-muted);
  color: var(--primer-fg-on-emphasis);
  &:hover {
    background-color: var(--primer-neutral-muted);
    filter: brightness(0.5);
  }
}
```

`className` is allowed ONLY for overriding Primer components. Custom components use `variant` props exclusively.

### Brightness for Color Variants

Use `filter: brightness()` to derive darker/lighter shades from `--primer-*` variables when no exact variable exists:

```scss
.rail { filter: brightness(0.75); }
.button:hover { filter: brightness(0.5); }
.activeIcon:hover { filter: brightness(0.85); }
```

## Exceptions â€” Raw HTML Allowed

Native HTML elements are acceptable ONLY when Primer has no equivalent:

- `<div>` for generic layout containers
- `<nav>`, `<aside>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<header>`, `<footer>` for semantic landmarks
- `<form>` for form wrappers
- Invisible overlays/backdrops (Primer has no backdrop component)
- NEVER use `<button>`, `<span>`, `<p>`, `<h1>`â€“`<h6>`, `<input>`, `<select>`, `<a>` â€” Primer has equivalents for all of these

## Component Mapping

| Need | Primer Component |
|------|-----------------|
| Buttons | `Button`, `IconButton` |
| Forms | `TextInput`, `Select`, `Checkbox`, `Radio`, `FormControl` |
| Layout | `PageLayout`, `SplitPageLayout` |
| Navigation | `NavList`, `UnderlineNav`, `Header` |
| Feedback | `Flash`, `Banner`, `Spinner`, `ProgressBar` |
| Overlays | `Dialog`, `ActionMenu`, `Overlay` |
| Data | `DataTable`, `Label`, `Token`, `TreeView` |
| Typography | `Heading`, `Text` |

## Atoms Wrapping Primer

Atoms wrap Primer components following the full component file structure (see component-structure rule):

```
atoms/Button/
  Button.tsx
  Button.module.scss
  Button.types.ts
  Button.utils.ts
  Button.test.tsx
  index.ts
```

```tsx
// atoms/Button/Button.types.ts
import type { ButtonProps as PrimerButtonProps } from '@primer/react'

export interface ButtonProps extends Pick<PrimerButtonProps, 'variant' | 'size' | 'disabled'> {
  label: string
  onClick: () => void
}
```

```tsx
// atoms/Button/Button.tsx
import { Button as PrimerButton } from '@primer/react'
import type { ButtonProps } from './Button.types'

export const Button = ({ label, ...rest }: ButtonProps) => (
  <PrimerButton {...rest}>{label}</PrimerButton>
)
```

